I once went on a road-trip in Yemen and spent the night sleeping in the empty-quarter desert, I had the most disturbing nightmares ever!

1- Well, I know this might sound a bit odd and random, but I have dreamt of Zeus mating with a palm tree and begetting an ant that is capable of crawling on the edge of the Higgs Boson!

2- I once also dreamt of my mitochondria protesting to break free from my organelles , claiming that nature has enslaved them !

3- On that night of a full moon, I dreamt of Professor Noam Chomsky eating books and regurgitating the field of Modern Linguistics!

4- The funniest dream I ever had, was when I had a vision of a Neanderthal swallowing a whole apple, and it played ping-pong with his heart while passing down his oesophagus!

5- The most disgusting dream I ever had, was of a female's menstruation blood turning into jelly and been marketed by an Oompa Loompa as Halloween treats!



I have absolutely no clue what caused me to have such nightmares, I have been left a little concerned that I'm having a neurological malfunction!

Given that I've heard my neurons conspiring to abandon the dwelling of my skull, things don't seem to be heading in the right direction, ever-since!

Best Iftar Restaurant: Abu Zaid (Foul, Matbaq, Masoub)
Saudi Restaurants: Al Baik (Broast), Al Tazaj (Grilled Chicken), Herfy (Burger)
Best fish restaurants in Thuwal
The Best Kabsa Restaurants: Raydan, Al Romansiah
Best dessert shop: Al-Mahawi, Saad Eddin
Top attractions: Jeddah Fountain, Lantern Square, Globe Square, Bike Square

The largest mall in Jeddah: Redsea Mall, Mall of Arabia, Al Salam Mall
You will find Arabic cafes in the mall. You can drink Arabic coffee with Ma'amoul, Klaija and dates
King Abdullah city in Thuwal is also beautiful
If you have questions about Islam, there is a missionary office in eastern Jeddah
Popular markets: Hay Al-Balad (Old Jeddah)
Al-Yamamah Markets, Al-Sharq Markets, Al-Bawadi Markets
